Rain-slick Harbor City is “kept afloat” by three powers. The Harbor Authority Guild publicly manages docks, permits, and safety audits; in truth it stages “accidents” to erase witnesses and steer contraband through favored berths. The Saint Brigid Mutual Aid Society runs soup lines and rent relief; behind the hymns it launders money and shelters runaways—some willingly, some not—making it both Lena’s best lead and worst blind spot. Over them sits the Meridian Assurance Combine, a respectable insurer funding civic reforms; secretly it engineers deaths to cash policies and pressure clients into dependency. The Combine bankrolls the Guild, the Society feeds it names, and all three quietly hunt whoever keeps surviving.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Harbor Authority Guild",
      "public_front": "Regulates docks, issues permits, conducts safety inspections, and coordinates harbor security.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Orchestrates “accidents” to eliminate witnesses, control shipping lanes, and protect a contraband pipeline."
    },
    {
      "name": "Saint Brigid Mutual Aid Society",
      "public_front": "Provides soup kitchens, rent relief, and sanctuary services in the tenements and waterfront parishes.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Launders money and runs a covert shelter/transport network for missing persons—some rescued, some coerced."
    },
    {
      "name": "Meridian Assurance Combine",
      "public_front": "Citywide insurance and pension provider sponsoring public-safety campaigns and civic modernization.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Engineers coordinated deaths for payouts and leverage, forcing businesses and families into long-term dependence."
    }
  ]
}
```

A dockworkers’ safety strike has choked Pier Nine after two “equipment failures” in a week; the Harbor Authority Guild responds with midnight inspections and quiet arrests, while Meridian Assurance agents offer “emergency coverage” that reads like a shakedown. At the same time, Saint Brigid’s soup line is overwhelmed by new runaways—some drugged, all missing paperwork—and Sister Calwen is moving them through the church crypts as Guild watchers prowl the alleys. Lena’s name is circulating in Combine claim offices, and a familiar face from her brother’s case has resurfaced near the harbor morgue.

